</span></span></span></p>
<h3 data-id=3D"2fff00009fc14a6c4e65ca8cfb13576d"><mark> Argument: </mark></=
h3>
<p data-id=3D"d0d3a9ccf11a9d3125407d626aeecc0d">Any Bash command takes a li=
st of arguments to indicate to the system which objects to look for while p=
erforming the action. An argument could be a string, set of string or a tok=
en passed to the command. For example, the command <code>ls</code> can take=
 a directory=E2=80=99s path as an argument.</p>
<pre class=3D"cm-viewer-markdown disable-cursor" style=3D"background-color:=
 #282830; border-radius: 4px;" data-id=3D"139f34652f7337652ee71aa30461d797"=
><code class=3D"language-Shell vsDark" data-lang=3D"shell"><span><span clas=
s=3D"mtk26">ls</span><span class=3D"mtk1">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"mtk11=
